This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on frame-semantic parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture that leverages recent advancements in language modeling and transfer learning, which are key areas of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses various experimental settings and performance metrics, which are common in the field of neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are widely used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing.
